@Host = http://localhost:5147
@ContentType = application/json

### 1. Initialize Meilisearch Settings
# This syncs our Type-Safe Filterable and Sortable attributes defined in MeiliConstants.
POST {{Host}}/setup
Content-Type: {{ContentType}}

###

### 2. Basic Search-as-you-type (Search Term Only)
# Testing the sub-20ms latency for a raw text query.
POST {{Host}}/search
Content-Type: {{ContentType}}

{
  "searchTerm": "Ferrari",
  "limit": 5
}

###

### 3. Advanced Faceted Filtering (Company + Price Range)
# Testing our "Business-Logic" filtering without magic strings.
POST {{Host}}/search
Content-Type: {{ContentType}}

{
  "searchTerm": "SF90",
  "company": "FERRARI",
  "minPrice": 500000,
  "maxPrice": 1500000,
  "limit": 10
}

###

### 4. Filter by Fuel Type
# Testing categorical discovery.
POST {{Host}}/search
Content-Type: {{ContentType}}

{
  "fuelType": "plug in hybrid",
  "limit": 5,
  "offset": 0
}

###

### 5. High-Performance Pagination
# Testing offset-based scrolling through the 1M+ car listings.
POST {{Host}}/search
Content-Type: {{ContentType}}

{
  "searchTerm": "V8",
  "limit": 20,
  "offset": 100
}

### Test Partial Search (Search-as-you-type)
# Typing "Fer" should return "Ferrari" matches immediately.
POST {{Host}}/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "searchTerm": "Fer",
  "limit": 3
}
